{
  "text": "G1: normal healthy animals G2-G5: animals orally administered 600 mg/kg body weight/day n-ZnO for 5 days [CITATION_1] , and divided as follows: G2:ZnO-intoxicated animals with a low oral dose (600 mg/kg/day) daily for 5 days. G3: ZnO-intoxicated animals administered Qur (200 mg/kg) daily [CITATION_2] . G4: ZnO-intoxicated animals administered Arg (200 mg/kg) [CITATION_3] daily. G5: ZnO-intoxicated animals co-administered Arg (200 mg/kg) and Qur (100 mg/kg) daily.",
